### Register User (Organiser)
POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Aisha Asif",
  "email": "aisha1@example.com",
  "password": "my very long secure passphrase",
  "role": "ORGANISER"
}


### Login User
POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "aisha1@example.com",
  "password": "my very long secure passphrase"
}

### Test Protected Route (Coming Soon)
GET http://127.0.0.1:5000/
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
### Create Event (Organiser only)
POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/events
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_YOUR_LOGIN_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "title": "AI Security Workshop",
  "description": "A detailed workshop on secure web development and authentication.",
  "eventDate": "2026-04-15T14:00:00.000Z",
  "capacity": 100,
  "venueId": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "categoryId": "PUT_CATEGORY_ID_HERE"
}